Understood. It's worth pointing out that using the 'nightly-gpu' container from the docker hub, I can't import the GBDTClassifier or the estimator python module:

Traceback (most recent call last):
File "/mnt/batch/tasks/shared/LS_root/mounts/azfileshare/scripts/train.py", line 9, in
import models
File "/mnt/batch/tasks/shared/LS_root/mounts/azfileshare/scripts/models.py", line 4, in
from tensorflow.contrib.boosted_trees.estimator_batch.estimator import GradientBoostedDecisionTreeClassifier
ImportError: No module named estimator

Using the '1.4.0-rc1' image works fine. I don't know if this is indicative of a problem introduced since the 1.4.0-rc1 image was cooked or not. It says it was updated 4 days ago.

body:
Understood.  It's worth pointing out that using the 'nightly-gpu' container from the [docker hub](https://hub.docker.com/r/tensorflow/tensorflow/tags/), I can't import the GBDTClassifier or the estimator python module:

Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "/mnt/batch/tasks/shared/LS_root/mounts/azfileshare/scripts/train.py", line 9, in <module>
    import models
  File "/mnt/batch/tasks/shared/LS_root/mounts/azfileshare/scripts/models.py", line 4, in <module>
    from tensorflow.contrib.boosted_trees.estimator_batch.estimator import GradientBoostedDecisionTreeClassifier
ImportError: No module named estimator

Using the '1.4.0-rc1' image works fine. I don't know if this is indicative of a problem introduced since the 1.4.0-rc1 image was cooked or not.  It says it was updated 4 days ago.
